244
00:18:34,360 --> 00:18:37,560
<i>I'm sorry, that is only half the truth.</i>

245
00:18:37,680 --> 00:18:41,720
I say in Zulu, <i>"Hayi khona, akunjalo,"</i>

246
00:18:41,840 --> 00:18:43,800
"No, it is not so."

247
00:18:44,440 --> 00:18:50,280
<i>This woman...
was a creature from the stars.</i>

248
00:18:50,400 --> 00:18:52,840
She also had proof...

249
00:18:53,600 --> 00:18:59,040
according to her,
of her visit to this other galaxy.

250
00:18:59,160 --> 00:19:03,440
No, it's not a different galaxy.
It's <i>our</i> galaxy, it's a different planet.

251
00:19:03,560 --> 00:19:07,040
<i>She showed me a thick...
almost like a book,</i>

252
00:19:07,160 --> 00:19:10,960
<i>which was sent to her
by the American Department of Defense,</i>

253
00:19:11,800 --> 00:19:15,880
<i>I think it was their Airforce branch,
which she had to fill in.</i>

254
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:19,840
<i>Every little finest detail
of her experience.</i>

255
00:19:19,960 --> 00:19:22,840
And it was 42 pages, A4.

256
00:19:22,960 --> 00:19:26,200
So, it was in extreme detail,

257
00:19:26,320 --> 00:19:28,680
<i>and I wondered
why were they so interested.</i>

258
00:19:28,800 --> 00:19:30,440
<i>Then I knew they were doing research</i>

259
00:19:30,560 --> 00:19:33,960
<i>and they were trying to find out
about such happenings.</i>

260
00:19:34,080 --> 00:19:39,360
She must've had her first intimations
or contact with flying saucers

261
00:19:39,480 --> 00:19:41,320
because she took these photographs.

262
00:19:41,440 --> 00:19:44,400
<i>Not particularly good, but I think it
was with an ordinary camera.</i>

263
00:19:45,280 --> 00:19:48,320
- [camera shutter clicks]
<i>- And those were the first ones that I know</i>

264
00:19:48,440 --> 00:19:51,920
<i>- that were photographed in 1956.</i>
- [flying saucer whirring]

265
00:20:02,880 --> 00:20:07,040
And I've had people say, "Well,
those look like ordinary baking pots

266
00:20:07,160 --> 00:20:09,720
that were thrown up into the air,"
or some stupid remark.

267
00:20:11,280 --> 00:20:14,720
[John] <i>Astronomers have since discovered
an earth-like planet</i>

268
00:20:14,840 --> 00:20:18,040
<i>in the Alpha Centauri constellation.</i>

269
00:20:18,160 --> 00:20:22,240
<i>There could be as many as 40 billion
Earth-sized planets</i>

270
00:20:22,360 --> 00:20:24,920
<i>orbiting in the habitable zones</i>

271
00:20:25,040 --> 00:20:30,680
<i>of sun-like stars and red dwarf stars
within the Milky Way galaxy.</i>

272
00:20:31,440 --> 00:20:34,000
<i>Ooh, we're definitely not alone.</i>

273
00:20:35,120 --> 00:20:40,720
There it is, Alpha Centauri, our nearest
neighbor, and 44-million years by taxi.

274
00:20:40,840 --> 00:20:45,360
<i>About 500 times further away
is the star Proxima Centauri.</i>

275
00:20:45,480 --> 00:20:49,120
The nearest star to us,
which hosts the planet Meton,

276
00:20:49,240 --> 00:20:51,520
according to Elizabeth Klarer,

277
00:20:51,640 --> 00:20:55,400
from where Akon,
the extraterrestrial visitor, is from.

278
00:20:55,520 --> 00:20:58,800
[John]<i>Dr. Enrico Olivier is an astronomer.</i>

279
00:20:58,920 --> 00:21:02,680
<i>Research areas include
the late stages of stellar evolution,</i>

280
00:21:02,800 --> 00:21:07,280
<i>non-linear modeling of stellar vibrations,
and brown dwarfs.</i>

281
00:21:07,400 --> 00:21:12,760
All of the things that I've seen...
that are strange to me in the night skies,

282
00:21:12,880 --> 00:21:16,200
I could've always explained it
afterwards or something,

283
00:21:16,320 --> 00:21:21,040
either natural or something man-made
that was happening up in the night sky.

284
00:21:21,160 --> 00:21:24,480
We found that when we traveled
around the area where she lived,

285
00:21:25,160 --> 00:21:29,040
<i>that the Zulu people often see
the flying saucers.</i>

286
00:21:29,160 --> 00:21:31,840
<i>- Mm.
- And they consider them to be gods.</i>

287
00:21:31,960 --> 00:21:37,360
<i>And when they see them, they fall down on
their knees and close their eyes and pray.</i>

288
00:21:37,480 --> 00:21:41,640
<i>They don't look up again
till they're sure that they're gone.</i>

289
00:21:42,920 --> 00:21:45,360
My sister phoned me one day and said,

290
00:21:45,840 --> 00:21:51,760
"The Zulus are seeing
what they call in their language,

291
00:21:51,880 --> 00:21:53,960
'The Wagon in the Sky.'"

292
00:21:54,920 --> 00:21:59,400
And... their folklore, of course...

293
00:21:59,520 --> 00:22:03,080
This also comes into their folklore,

294
00:22:03,200 --> 00:22:08,440
and the correct Zulu name
for the flying saucer

295
00:22:08,560 --> 00:22:11,280
is "The Lightning Bird".

296
00:22:12,200 --> 00:22:16,120
[John]<i>Beyond the Light Barrier, page 14...</i>

297
00:22:16,840 --> 00:22:20,680
"Ikhanya elikhanya emnyameni."

298
00:22:21,520 --> 00:22:26,800
<i>"A light that enlightened the darkness."
A Zulu praise.</i>

299
00:22:27,480 --> 00:22:30,960
My sister again phoned me and said,
"You'd better come down

300
00:22:31,080 --> 00:22:33,760
because the Lightning Bird
again is in the sky

301
00:22:33,880 --> 00:22:35,920
- and the Zulus are very excited."
- [serene music]

302
00:22:36,040 --> 00:22:38,840
I don't think
there's any other case on record

303
00:22:38,960 --> 00:22:44,240
of a woman giving birth
to a child from an alien.

304
00:22:44,360 --> 00:22:46,280
Pure undiluted love.

305
00:22:46,400 --> 00:22:50,480
I mean, there must've been a passion
that we can't even imagine.

306
00:22:50,600 --> 00:22:55,000
And what she gave up,
and the way she transported herself.

307
00:22:55,120 --> 00:22:58,760
I mean, that has got to be one of the
greatest love stories we'll never know.

308
00:22:58,880 --> 00:23:00,240
[gentle music]

309
00:23:07,880 --> 00:23:10,120
- [camera shutter clicks]
- [Paul] <i>That's not a good love story.</i>

310
00:23:10,720 --> 00:23:12,560
<i>That's not a good love story at all.</i>

311
00:23:12,680 --> 00:23:15,360
He comes, impregnates her,
brings her back,

312
00:23:15,480 --> 00:23:19,040
takes the baby and never sees her again.
That's not a good love story.

313
00:23:22,760 --> 00:23:26,480
[John]<i>Now, Paul Brogan has been many things.</i>

314
00:23:26,600 --> 00:23:32,440
<i>An engineer, stockbroker,
company executive, environmentalist,</i>

315
00:23:32,560 --> 00:23:35,920
<i>community leader, skeptic, and writer.</i>

316
00:23:36,040 --> 00:23:39,840
<i>Things he's not? A UFO-hugger.</i>

317
00:23:39,960 --> 00:23:42,040
<i>A good love story is my wife and I.</i>

318
00:23:42,160 --> 00:23:46,120
We get married and we stay together
for the rest of our natural lives.

319
00:23:46,240 --> 00:23:49,200
That's a love story.
And that happens every day.

320
00:23:50,320 --> 00:23:53,880
Why are we not glorifying that?
This is not a love story to be glorified

321
00:23:54,000 --> 00:23:57,880
or to be admired or to be copied.
Not at all. Not in my opinion

322
00:23:58,480 --> 00:24:02,000
He said, "Now we're going
to the high plateau at Cathkin,"

323
00:24:02,120 --> 00:24:05,400
because there was an air force plane,

324
00:24:06,440 --> 00:24:08,400
one of these Harvard planes,

325
00:24:08,520 --> 00:24:13,720
an old air force plane,
droning around the sky all the time.

326
00:24:13,840 --> 00:24:17,120
And he said, "Let's get away from that."
And we went up.

327
00:24:17,240 --> 00:24:20,120
And he took me up
to the high plateau at Cathkin.

328
00:24:20,240 --> 00:24:23,480
We have guests who come here
to stay with us especially...

329
00:24:24,480 --> 00:24:27,280
to go and visit the UFO landing site...

330
00:24:28,200 --> 00:24:32,880
<i>where Akon or Arkon, I don't even know
how to pronounce his name,</i>

331
00:24:33,000 --> 00:24:34,400
<i>seduced his little earthling</i>

332
00:24:34,520 --> 00:24:40,160
<i>and swept her up into his arms
or tentacles or whatever,</i>

333
00:24:40,280 --> 00:24:44,080
<i>and took her off to Alpha Centauri.</i>

334
00:24:44,200 --> 00:24:47,680
<i>And they've met her,
and they believe her story.</i>

335
00:24:48,160 --> 00:24:49,920
<i>Unfortunately, I haven't met her.</i>

336
00:24:50,040 --> 00:24:56,120
<i>And being a skeptic,
being someone who doesn't easily...</i>

337
00:24:58,240 --> 00:25:00,600
<i>believe in the irrational...</i>

338
00:25:01,520 --> 00:25:03,240
<i>I have to...</i> [sighs]

339
00:25:03,360 --> 00:25:09,040
<i>I have to treat her story
with... with... with some... reserve.</i>

340
00:25:10,640 --> 00:25:12,680
[gentle music]

341
00:25:13,320 --> 00:25:16,800
[John] <i>Paul Brogan's home
is the highest inhabited property</i>

342
00:25:16,920 --> 00:25:19,360
<i>in the Central Drakensberg,</i>

343
00:25:19,480 --> 00:25:25,320
<i>the last friendly hearth before one
ascends into the vast mountain wilderness,</i>

344
00:25:25,440 --> 00:25:28,560
<i>and half-a-day's hike from the fastness,</i>

345
00:25:28,680 --> 00:25:33,640
<i>the alleged spaceship landing spot
of Cathkin Peak itself.</i>

346
00:25:42,800 --> 00:25:45,360
Behind me is Cathkin Peak.

347
00:25:46,920 --> 00:25:49,760
It's roughly 3000m up.

348
00:25:51,080 --> 00:25:56,120
On the top is a flat portion of land,
about the size of a soccer field...

349
00:25:58,040 --> 00:26:00,160
and up there, allegedly...

350
00:26:01,880 --> 00:26:04,280
a spaceman called Akon...

351
00:26:05,280 --> 00:26:09,320
flew his "earthling" girlfriend,
Elizabeth Klarer...

352
00:26:10,360 --> 00:26:11,480
to the top...

353
00:26:12,640 --> 00:26:14,920
and they made mad, passionate love...

354
00:26:16,120 --> 00:26:19,520
<i>and she conceived a child up there,
a boy, apparently.</i>

355
00:26:21,160 --> 00:26:22,880
<i>And where the spaceship landed...</i>

356
00:26:24,040 --> 00:26:28,200
<i>there is a bare patch of ground,
where nothing grows.</i>

357
00:26:29,600 --> 00:26:33,840
<i>I don't know whether the spaceship caused
that, but I suspect there are perfectly...</i>

358
00:26:34,600 --> 00:26:37,680
<i>plausible, geological reasons
for nothing growing there.</i>

359
00:26:37,800 --> 00:26:42,840
<i>The plausible reason would be that water
has leached through this soil,</i>

360
00:26:42,960 --> 00:26:47,120
<i>leached out all the nutrients,
so there's just sand left,</i>

361
00:26:48,080 --> 00:26:53,520
<i>and that... Then there's nothing left
to nourish grass and trees, and so on.</i>

362
00:26:53,640 --> 00:26:55,200
[ominous music]

363
00:26:58,520 --> 00:27:01,960
[John] <i>And yet, here we find ourselves
with a photo</i>

364
00:27:02,080 --> 00:27:07,120
<i>taken long before spaceships allegedly
landed on Cathkin Peak plateau,</i>

365
00:27:07,240 --> 00:27:13,680
<i>where one can clearly see lush vegetation
and plant life covering the area</i>

366
00:27:13,800 --> 00:27:17,320
<i>before a UFO crossed their plant paths.</i>

367
00:27:19,120 --> 00:27:23,720
<i>This is Akon... who was my mother's love.</i>

368
00:27:23,840 --> 00:27:27,720
<i>Also ostensibly the father of Ayling,</i>

369
00:27:28,800 --> 00:27:31,600
<i>my mother's other son, who I've never met.</i>

370
00:27:32,240 --> 00:27:36,080
It seems I have a half-brother
out there in space.

371
00:27:39,040 --> 00:27:43,160
And... But I do have doubts
about this story.

372
00:27:43,280 --> 00:27:46,960
<i>I have my doubts
that my mother's story is true,</i>

373
00:27:47,080 --> 00:27:49,760
<i>in terms of her meeting with Akon
and going up into space</i>

374
00:27:49,880 --> 00:27:52,600
<i>and having a child, all that. Um...</i>

375
00:27:53,480 --> 00:27:56,480
I find it very frustrating
that there's no out-and-out proof for me.

376
00:27:56,600 --> 00:28:00,280
I would've really liked to have known
which way this whole story goes.

377
00:28:00,400 --> 00:28:02,680
Was it true? Was it not true? [chuckles]

378
00:28:02,800 --> 00:28:04,800
But certain things have occurred, um...

379
00:28:05,640 --> 00:28:07,520
certain writings in her book,
certain events.

380
00:28:08,120 --> 00:28:11,680
And a major one for me
was one where she says that I was involved

381
00:28:11,800 --> 00:28:14,720
up in the Drakensberg
and a craft landed in front of us.

382
00:28:14,840 --> 00:28:18,280
We were up there on horseback
and this craft landed in front of us

383
00:28:18,400 --> 00:28:21,880
and Akon got out. And I don't recall that.

384
00:28:23,040 --> 00:28:27,600
[Elizabeth] <i>So I rode off, and...
With a groom and a packhorse,</i>

385
00:28:27,720 --> 00:28:29,680
<i>and, of course, David with me as well.</i>

386
00:28:29,800 --> 00:28:32,600
<i>And that's when I met him again.</i>

387
00:28:32,720 --> 00:28:35,640
Now, surely, something like that at my...

388
00:28:36,560 --> 00:28:39,480
even young age of, let's say,
eight or nine years old,

389
00:28:39,600 --> 00:28:40,960
I'd have remembered something like that

390
00:28:41,080 --> 00:28:43,200
because other parts of that trip
I do remember.

391
00:28:43,320 --> 00:28:48,160
The idea of Akon having erased
the memory out of my mind in some way

392
00:28:48,280 --> 00:28:49,640
has crossed my mind...

393
00:28:50,720 --> 00:28:54,120
But then I ask myself, "Why would he have
done it? What was the purpose?"

394
00:28:54,240 --> 00:28:58,080
Especially as she says in her book, she
needs to get this story out to the world.

395
00:28:58,200 --> 00:29:02,040
Surely, I would've been a witness.
I would've supported her and...

396
00:29:02,920 --> 00:29:05,800
backed her up
on that story totally, wholeheartedly,

397
00:29:05,920 --> 00:29:09,360
if I'd seen that craft landing
and if I'd met Akon as well.

398
00:29:09,480 --> 00:29:10,480
Fantastic.

399
00:29:11,160 --> 00:29:16,000
[Elizabeth]
Now this one is of the same starship...

400
00:29:16,720 --> 00:29:19,720
moving up into the higher atmosphere.

401
00:29:19,840 --> 00:29:23,480
And owing to the moisture content
in the atmosphere,

402
00:29:23,600 --> 00:29:26,520
there is cloud condensed around her again.

403
00:29:26,640 --> 00:29:30,360
<i>This cameraman, he was so surprised.</i>

404
00:29:30,480 --> 00:29:34,720
<i>And I explained to him
that if he'd taken it a second later,</i>

405
00:29:34,840 --> 00:29:37,520
<i>he would've got the whole figure</i>

406
00:29:37,640 --> 00:29:42,520
<i>of Akon standing there beside me
in a hologram.</i>

407
00:29:43,840 --> 00:29:49,120
[John] <i>Pity there are no photos of Akon.
All we have is a painting,</i>

408
00:29:49,240 --> 00:29:53,560
<i>where he looks very much
like a male version of Elizabeth.</i>

409
00:29:53,680 --> 00:29:56,520
He won't be photographed.
He doesn't want to be arrested

410
00:29:56,640 --> 00:29:59,800
and put into laboratories,
pins stuck in him, and needles,

411
00:29:59,920 --> 00:30:02,840
to find out what makes him tick
as an alien.

412
00:30:02,960 --> 00:30:05,440
He avoids that, of course.

413
00:30:05,560 --> 00:30:09,680
And it also enables him to meet Elizabeth
regularly in those years.

414
00:30:11,280 --> 00:30:17,920
[John] <i>And a bust of our alien in question
made by sculpture Bob Forbes.</i>

415
00:30:20,360 --> 00:30:23,360
[Bob] I just had the feeling
that if I called on Akon himself,

416
00:30:23,480 --> 00:30:27,520
that he might possibly be able to help me.
And that's exactly what I did.

417
00:30:27,640 --> 00:30:31,120
I called on him, and within three hours,

418
00:30:31,240 --> 00:30:35,320
I'd actually completed
this sculpture in clay,

419
00:30:35,440 --> 00:30:37,080
which normally takes three weeks.

420
00:30:38,080 --> 00:30:43,480
We called Elizabeth to have a look at it.
I didn't know whether it was him or not.

421
00:30:44,320 --> 00:30:47,480
<i>And when she saw the sculpture,</i>

422
00:30:47,600 --> 00:30:50,840
<i>she was obviously very, very excited.</i>

423
00:30:50,960 --> 00:30:55,640
<i>Very, very happy. And it was quite obvious
that it was in fact him.</i>

424
00:30:55,760 --> 00:30:58,280
Then the most amazing thing,
about a week later,

425
00:30:58,400 --> 00:31:03,840
my son was sitting in the front room
of the house looking out to the horizon,

426
00:31:03,960 --> 00:31:07,800
and he saw a whole series of lights
bobbing up and down

427
00:31:07,920 --> 00:31:11,080
where they shouldn't have been.
And he called us all.

428
00:31:11,200 --> 00:31:14,040
In fact, the whole family,
we all went rushing out.

429
00:31:14,160 --> 00:31:18,080
And we saw these lights.
Thirteen of them on the horizon,

430
00:31:18,200 --> 00:31:21,680
bobbing up and down and very, very bright.

431
00:31:21,800 --> 00:31:25,240
And then one by one, they popped off.

